<text>
<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Two  <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">architrave</rs> blocks, one complete  (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.57</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.42</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.58</measure>) and one broken away at the right end and damaged above (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.99</measure> x <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.42</measure> x <measure dim="depth" type="length" unit="metre">0.59</measure>), slightly curving, both with simple moulding above and between the two fasciae.</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p>The first is <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">inscribed</rs> on both fasciae (ll.1 and 2 on upper, l. 3 on lower), the second on the upper one only; the texts have been erased at the left end of ll. 1 and 2, and are interrupted by a bad flaw in the stone.</p>
</div><div type="description" n="letters"><head>Description of letters</head><p>Standard forms; ll.1, 2, <measure dim="none">0.048</measure>; l.3, <measure dim="none">0.05</measure>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date cert="low" notAfter="0150" notBefore="0101" exact="none"> Probably first half of second century A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="left" unit="character"/><w lemma="καί">καὶ</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μελίτιος">Μελίτιον</name>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Πυθίων">Πυθίω<milestone unit="block"/>νος</name></persName></persName>  <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="left" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved">ν</orig>  <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w>  <w lemma="ὁ">τ<gap extent="1" dim="internal" reason="lost" unit="character" id="gap04"/><certainty target="gap04" locus="#gi" degree="low" assertedValue="space"/>ὰ</w>  <w lemma="ἐν">ἐν</w>  <w lemma="αὐτός">αὐτοῖς</w>  <milestone unit="block"/>    <w lemma="πᾶς">πάντα</w> <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="left" unit="character"/>  <w lemma="ἐκ"><supplied reason="lost">ἐκ</supplied></w>  <w lemma="ὁ"><supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied>ῶν</w>  <w lemma="ἴδιος">ἰδίων</w>  <gap reason="lost" extent="2" unit="character" dim="internal"/><space extent="7" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><milestone unit="block"/> <space extent="1" unit="line" dim="horizontal"/></ab>
</div>

<div type="apparatus">
<head>Apparatus</head>
<p>l. 2,  apparently a fault in the stone between <foreign lang="grc">Τ</foreign> and <foreign lang="grc">Α</foreign>.</p>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="left" unit="character"/> and Melition daughter of Pythion made the <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="internal" unit="character"/> and everything in them   <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="internal" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">at</supplied> their own expense <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" dim="right" unit="character"/></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary" n="none">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>
There is insufficient evidence to show what was built but it should be noted that it is described by a plural pronoun. The builders are likely to have been a man (name lost) and his wife who is not at present identifiable.</p>
</div>
